entry.title: A possible biosynthesis pathway of arctigenin in Arctium lappa L.
entry.content:
It is a potential pathway of arctigenin biosynthesis in _Arctium lappa L._. ,

​ This assumption is based on:

[1] Chan, Y. S., Cheng, L. N., Wu, J. H., Chan, E., Kwan, Y. W., Lee, S. M., Leung, G. P., Yu, P. H., & Chan, S. W. (2011). A review of the pharmacological effects of Arctium lappa (burdock). Inflammopharmacology, 19(5), 245–254.

[2] Morimoto, K., & Satake, H. (2013). Seasonal alteration in amounts of lignans and their glucosides and gene expression of the relevant biosynthetic enzymes in the Forsythia suspense leaf. Biological & pharmaceutical bulletin, 36(9), 1519–1523.

[3] Ozawa, S., Davin, L. B., & Lewis, N. G. (1993). Formation of (−)-arctigenin in Forsythia intermedia. Phytochemistry, 32(3), 643-652.

​ Due to the fact that caffeyl alcohol (zh: 咖啡醇) is abundant in _Actrium lappa L._, we set the substrate as caffeyl alcohol.
